<h2><a name="flags" id="flags">flags</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    fmtflags stream<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">flags</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
    fmtflags stream<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">flags</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> fmtflags f <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>

The flags() function either returns the io_stream_format_flags for the current
stream, or sets the flags for the current stream to be f.
</p>

<p>
Related Topics: <a href="setf" class="wikilink1" title="io:setf">setf</a>, <a href="unsetf" class="wikilink1" title="io:unsetf">unsetf</a>
</p>

